Kim Hang is the youngest designer to show at Mercedes-Benz Fashion Week Australia . 
  The Brisbane-based designer is committed to improving working conditions in Cambodia . 
  He is inspired by his Cambodian heritage and his parents escaped the Khmer Rouge . 
  The 22-year-old opened a factory in his home country to look after his workers . 
  He displayed his collection HAN at Carriageworks in Sydney . 
 